@endnode

@node "Localezation" "Localezation"

    OEL uses localezation to present the user in her prefered language.  It
  also make it possible to easily add support for another language through
  the use of catalogs.

    For more information on localezation and the Locale preference editor
  see the Workbench manual that came with your Amiga computer.


    There are 2 ways to make a new catalog:

    1.  You could edit an existing catalog with a utility like CatEdit.

    2.  Edit the catalog translation file and "compile" a new catalog file
        with FlexCat.  For this purpose ErrorMessages.cd (the catalog
        description file) and ErrorMessages.ct (the catalog translation
        file) is included with the OEL archive.        
@endnode

@node "ARexxExamples" "ARexx examples"

